From cou.: 12 For shear orientation of very small volumes of lyotropic phases, lithographically patterned microfluidic channel grids were used (Fig. 5). These grids consist of parallel aligned micron-sized channels with variable width and depth. They were produced by standard soft lithographic techniques from a PDMS master, which was used as a mold for NOA81 (Norland Optical Adhesive). NOA 81 is a UV-curable adhesive and more solvent-resisting than PDMS,17–19 especially to toluene. For the measurements, an amount of 2–5 μL of the sample was spread on the microstructured grid. The grid was taped with Kapton to prevent solvent evaporation.
From Soup: 12 For shear orientation of very small volumes of lyotropic phases, lithographically patterned microfluidic channel grids were used ( Fig. 5 ). These grids consist of parallel aligned micron-sized channels with variable width and depth. They were produced by standard soft lithographic techniques from a PDMS master, which was used as a mold for NOA81 (Norland Optical Adhesive). NOA 81 is a UV-curable adhesive and more solvent -resisting than PDMS, 17–19 especially to toluene . For the measurements, an amount of 2–5 μL of the sample was spread on the microstructured grid. The grid was taped with Kapton to prevent solvent evaporation .
